<subSubSection id="41A71E9241F62B26290EEC136B1F78F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="0177DA060AC7C27F70A79C619AD9B2C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="101">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D67821E26F8C336A520F5F4DBEC3064B" pageId="0" pageNumber="101">
In the New World reared as hyperparasitoid of 
<taxonomicName id="4D0025F10DE6A71BFC8290DAA349EC06" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ichneumonidae</taxonomicName>
in caterpillars of the families 
<taxonomicName id="0D4AE84F5680D224117543A9D48DA9D3" class="Insecta" family="Saturniidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Saturniidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="311498CFBADDEAC6D06E3FA3FCE8BEAB" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodontidae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="16EEA98AAC410EF42F29F1C65DF67E7D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.1998.00042.x" author="Carmean, D" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" pagination="35 - 76" refId="B2" refString="Carmean, D, Kimsey, L, 1998. Phylogenetic revision of the parasitoid wasp family Trigonalidae (Hymenoptera). Systematic Entomology 23: 35 - 76, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.1998.00042.x" title="Phylogenetic revision of the parasitoid wasp family Trigonalidae (Hymenoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.1998.00042.x" volume="23" year="1998">Carmean and Kimsey 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1416BAA00E451897C42C1A1BBEBE6D6F" pageId="0" pageNumber="101" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8FAB58B9A7261FEE062A7A43320B170B" pageId="0" pageNumber="101">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00F4765EE8078DEB3D9F688D67BB73A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="101">China. Before this study, four species of this genus have been described from China, with only one species recorded from Yunnan. We describe here the second species new to science from Yunnan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
